-- Petro Ivoire Opens Gas Terminal in Ivory Coast
-- B y   B a u d e l a i r e   M i e u
-- 2012-03-29T09:57:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-29/petro-ivoire-opens-gas-terminal-in-ivory-coast-correct-.html
(Corrects to show liquefied petroleum gas and corrects
title in first paragraph.)  Petro Ivoire SA, a fuel retailer in
 Ivory Coast , began operating a liquefied petroleum gas terminal
with a 1,500 metric-ton capacity in the port of Abidjan
yesterday, said Mathieu Kadio Moroko, president of the company.  Petro Ivoire and Geogas Trading SA, a Geneva-based LPG
trader, invested 6.5 billion CFA francs in the plant, Moroko
said in an interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Baudelaire Mieu in Abidjan at 
 bmieu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Emily Bowers at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net  